Whatever happens, the person in care will still have to pay the majority of their income each week towards their care, however much capital they may or may not have. Currently a person can keep £24.90 of income for “extras” in life such as toiletries, newspapers and hairdressing'

It is important to remember that the cap ONLY relates to care costs and not those for accommodation or food and there are no details yet on what the government will suggest those should be charged at.
Unfortunately the new rules are still somewhat light on details so it may be sometime before it is clear what someone will actually have to pay torwards their own costs.

Given the complexity of the scheme it would not be a surprise if there were more amendments before October 2023 when the new rules will come into effect.  Those already in care or who enter care before 1 October 2023 will not benefit from the new rules.
